meta {
  name: Test Media Upload Limits
  type: http
  seq: 9
}

post {
  url: {{baseUrl}}/api/messages
  body: multipartForm
  auth: bearer
}

auth:bearer {
  token: {{authToken}}
}

body:multipart-form {
  chatSessionId: your-chat-session-id
  messageType: image
  content: Testing upload limits - this should work
  images: @file(C:\path\to\small-image1.jpg)
  images: @file(C:\path\to\small-image2.jpg)
  images: @file(C:\path\to\small-image3.jpg)
}

docs {
  # Test Media Upload Limits
  
  This endpoint tests various media upload scenarios and limits.
  
  ## Test Scenarios:
  
  ### Valid Upload (should succeed):
  - 1-5 images
  - Each image < 5MB
  - Total < 10MB
  - Supported formats (JPG, PNG, GIF, WebP)
  
  ### Invalid Uploads (should fail):
  - More than 5 images
  - Single image > 5MB
  - Total upload > 10MB
  - Unsupported formats (PDF, TXT, etc.)
  
  ## Expected Errors:
  - `400`: "Maximum 5 images allowed per message"
  - `400`: "File size exceeds 5MB limit"
  - `400`: "Total upload size exceeds 10MB limit"
  - `400`: "Invalid file format. Allowed: jpg, jpeg, png, gif, webp"
  
  ## To Test Different Scenarios:
  1. Change number of files in form data
  2. Use different file sizes
  3. Try different file formats
  4. Test with/without content field
}